<TITLE> Commission submits twin recommendations to CA Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 02 (bdnews24.com)  The Regulatory Reforms Commission will submit twin recommendations to chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Monday, its chairman Akbar Ali Khan said. The recommendations are: To post all gazette notifications on the website and take public opinion before changing or introducing new rules or regulations. "The government changes rules and regulations frequently, which may affect people and businesses negatively," the former caretaker government finance adviser told reporters Sunday after a meeting with finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam at the planning ministry. "We will ask the government to take public opinion for proposed changes to rules and regulations to avert a negative impact," he said. He said people have the right to know "what would be changed and why". The interim administration in a major policy decision formed the 17-member commission on Oct 30 to update the ages-old rules and regulations to infuse dynamism into the economy, governance and administration. The tenure of the commission is one year. The commission held its first board meeting on Nov 18. bd
